# PulseWatch OSS Conventions

Same product stack as the private PulseWatch repo, but **this tree must stay desensitized**.

## Stack

- **Backend**: Go (`apps/api/`) — Gin, pgx, JWT, in-process scheduler
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 (`apps/web/`) — Tailwind 4, next-intl, `[locale]` App Router
- **Database**: PostgreSQL only — time-series in partitioned `check_results`
- **Mini program**: `apps/miniprogram/` — configure `config/env.js` and WeChat AppID locally

## i18n

- Locales: `en`, `zh` — keys in `messages/en.json` and `messages/zh.json`

## Security

- Never commit `环境信息`, `.env`, or real passwords
- Example hosts: `YOUR_SERVER_IP`, `example.pulsewatch.io` — replace in your own `.env` only

## Deploy (self-host)

```bash
export DEPLOY_HOST=your.server.ip
export DEPLOY_PASSWORD=your-ssh-password
export APP_DOMAINS=your.domain.com
export NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your.domain.com
cd deploy && node deploy.js   # first time
cd deploy && node redeploy-api.js
cd deploy && node redeploy-web.js
```

## Monitors CRUD

- Create: `/monitors/new` → POST
- Edit: `/monitors/[id]/edit` → PATCH
- Detail: `/monitors/[id]`

## Product UI

- Premium dark-mode SaaS; English keys + next-intl translations
- Marketing/landing changes: update `landing` namespace in message JSON and `landing-page.tsx` when shipping user-facing features
